Quote: There are two deepwater flatfishes in our waters.  The spotted flounder, <i>Azygopus pinnifasciatus</i> is widespread in 300-800 m. ... The finless flounder, <i>Mancopsetta milfordi</i>, is a left-eyed flounder of the Campbell Plateau ...
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1982
Source: Collins Guide
Author: AYLING
Vol / Page: 313
Edition: 1984
Quote: SPOTTED FLOUNDER <i>Azygopus pinnifasciatus </i>... This small deepwater flounder ...is easily distinguished from all other flounders by its colour pattern: the pale brown body is conspicuously marked with small dark spots on the upper surface and there is a dark spot on each side of the end of the tail fin.
